			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~thesandbender">thesandbender</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~thesandbender">( 911391 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64212314">		
		on Sunday February 04, 2024 @06:04AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//linux.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23215110&amp;cid=64212314">#64212314</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64212314">While I'm no fan of Microsoft, you can't win in a situation like this.<br> <br>
1. Don't upgrade dependencies and half the people will yell at you for not supporting new features, security, etc.<br>
2. Upgrade dependencies and the other half will yell at you for breaking their sh*t.<br> <br>
18.04 LTS expired last year.  You're running outdated software that you got for free and can upgrade for free.  Stop b*tching at Microsoft.  Yes, they have ESM (Extended Security Maintenance) but you have to pay for it and it's just security patches.<br> <br>
Your running on Linux.  You have a two options here:<br> <br>
1. Upgrade Ubuntu.<br>
2. Build glibc 2.28... it's not... that... hard.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64212314">
